  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">We report on a recent next-to-leading order perturbative determination of the dilepton rate from a hot QCD plasma for frequency and momentum of the order of the temperature and for much smaller invariant mass <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>M</mi><mo>âˆ¼</mo><mi>g</mi><mi>T</mi></math> . We briefly review the calculation, which generalizes the previous one for the photon case ( <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>M</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> ). We then analyze the consequences of the new calculation for the extraction of the photon rate from the small mass dilepton measurements. We then review a recent NLO determination at large M and we show how to match and merge its results with the low-mass ones, resulting in a single rate which is NLO-accurate over the phenomenologically relevant region.</subfield>
